{"lemma":"شامَةُ","slug":"شامَةُ","root":"ش.#.م","root_slug":"ش-_-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21499","n23564"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mole, naevus, natural mark on the body"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃaː.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21499","headword_ar":"شَاْمَةٌ","root":"$A^m","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oA^amapN","text_ar":"مَشْاَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left side"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relative location"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasorapN","text_ar":"يَسْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mayosarapN","text_ar":"مَيْسَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamonapN","text_ar":"يَمْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mayomanapN","text_ar":"مَيْمَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) One says of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEada","text_ar":"قَعَدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$A^omapN","text_ar":"شاْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sat on the left"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o bihimo $aA^omapF","text_ar":"خُذْ بِهِمْ شَاْمَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou with them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the direction of the left hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naZarotu yamonapF","text_ar":"نَظَرْتُ يَمْنَةً"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa$aA^omapF","text_ar":"وَشَاْمَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I looked in a right direction and in a left direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And hence ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoHaAbu Alma$oA^amapi","text_ar":"اَصْحَابُ المَشْاَمَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lvi. 9 and xc. 19], (TA,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The occupants of the left:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those who shall have their records given to them in their left hands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the occupants of the low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignoble, place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the havers of unfortunateness"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uw^om","text_ar":"الشُّوْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"): and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoHaAbu Almayomanapi","text_ar":"اَصْحَابُ المَيْمَنَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. as having the contr. senses. (Ksh and Bd in lvi. 9.)       -A2-  Also, the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mole"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAlN","text_ar":"خَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", as mentioned by IAth: also mentioned without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ym","text_ar":"شيم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAmapN","text_ar":"شَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning “ a black she-camel, ” in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ym","text_ar":"شيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n23564","headword_ar":"شَامَةٌ","root":"$ym","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAlN","text_ar":"خَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) upon the person; (Msb;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pimple inclining to blackness, upon the person;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark differing from the colour of the person upon which it is:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) its medial radical letter is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) and it is"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1635},{"kind":"text","text":"also with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA^omapN","text_ar":"شَاْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth, TA:) pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAmN","text_ar":"شَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) [or rather this is a coll. gen. n.,] and [the pl. properly so termed is]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAmaAtN","text_ar":"شَامَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY takuwnuwA kaA^an~akumo $aAmapN fiY Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"حَتَّى تَكُونُوا كَاَنَّكُمْ شَامَةٌ فِى النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"So that ye may be as though ye were a mole amid the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"], occurring in a trad., means [that ye may] be in the goodliest garb or guise, appearing like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Amp","text_ar":"شامة"},{"kind":"text","text":", at which one looks exclusively of the rest of the person. (IAth, TA.) And one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAruwA $aAmFA","text_ar":"صَارُوا شَامًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlbilaAdi","text_ar":"فِى البِلَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They became scattered"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the countries"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Am","text_ar":"شام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moles"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the person."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A black mark upon the person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an explanation which seems to apply, like the former in the K, to a mole, though given as differing therefrom,] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. [or coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAmN","text_ar":"شَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  It is also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a mare, upon a place that is disapproved, and sometimes upon her"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAy^ir","text_ar":"دَوَايِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means what are termed"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feathers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^irapN","text_ar":"دَايِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]. (ISh, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A spot"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukotap","text_ar":"نُكْتَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the face"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the moon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A black she-camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K, TA:) accord. to Niftaweyh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA^omapN","text_ar":"شَاْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with; but ISd says, I know not the reason of this, unless it be extr., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaA^otamu","text_ar":"الخَاْتَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaA^olimu","text_ar":"العَاْلِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lahu $aAmapN walaA zahoraA='u","text_ar":"مَا لَهُ شَامَةٌ وَلَا زَهْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has not a black she-camel nor a white one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","IAth","K","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}